   <abstract>Laura La Plante, Ruth Clifford, Clarence Brown, an unidentified man, and Kenneth Harlan on the set of "Butterfly" (1924). The movie was based on Kathleen Norris' novel of the same name and deals with Butterfly (Laura La Plante), who could be a great violinist if she would commit herself to serious study, and Hilary (Ruth Clifford), who sacrifices herself for her beloved sister.</abstract>
